snippet.textDisplay:
drums are over done in some places, many places rolls were not required 
Bass - tremendous,very groovy 
guy in black shervaani vocals - very nice and powerful vocals... has taken some places really beautifully, he has good range with base and high notes.
guy in black kurta vocals - nice soft voice texture, and he took one place that was really roller coaster harkat..... tremendous ...
overall i would rate it 8 out of 10. 
Sarangi solo should have been used more and it was little low to keep up the soul
Guitar solo didn't blend with the feel at all

Again this is my opinion - and its subjective, not necessary what i dislike or like will have the same reflection on you.

IF i listen to this song without thinking bout the technicality ..... its one amazing number... 

Bassist has done a marvelous job

ok not because i am Indian ,but i myself is a musician, i must say the Indian Naina more (peekaboo) is more subtle and perfectly executed with a blend of hip hop and jazz...... and the taste of raga is still in its pure form. you must listen to it... called Peekaboo by karsh kale
